* VibroSense PGA Folded-Cascode OTA — SKY130A
* High-current variant for ~50 kHz UGB at 10 pF
* Derived from ota_foldcasc v11 — same topology, same 9-pin interface
*
* Changes from filter OTA:
*   M11 W: 3.8u -> 11.4u (3x tail current at same Vbn)
*   M3/M4: 20 -> 50 instances (fold must exceed input + cascode)
*   M12/M13: W=0.42u (same as fold — preserves narrow-channel Vth)
*   M9/M10: W=2.15u -> 3.5u (higher cascode current for SR > 30 mV/us)
*
* Current balance: I_fold(~1275nA) = I_M1(~817nA) + I_cascode(~458nA)

.subckt ota_pga vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp

* Input Pair (W=5u L=14u for low 1/f noise)
XM1 fold_p vinp tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=5u L=14u nf=1
XM2 fold_n vinn tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=5u L=14u nf=1

* Tail (~1.6uA) — 3x width for 3x current at same Vbn
XM11 tail vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=11.4u L=14u nf=1

* PMOS Fold: 50 parallel instances of W=0.42u L=20u per branch
* (Narrow W critical for SKY130 PMOS Vth reduction — do NOT widen)
* Left branch (fold_p)
XM3a  fold_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1
