* PMOS Bias Mirrors (W=0.42u same as fold — preserves narrow-channel Vth)
XM12 fold_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1
XM13 fold_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1

* PMOS Cascode (W=0.84u L=2u — widened to reduce Vsg, keeps fold PMOS in saturation)
XM5  cas_p vbcp fold_p vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.84u L=2u nf=1
XM6  vout  vbcp fold_n vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.84u L=2u nf=1

* NMOS Cascode (W=2u L=14u) — unchanged
XM7  cas_p vbcn src7 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=14u nf=1
XM8  vout  vbcn src8 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=14u nf=1

* NMOS Current Sources (W=3.5u L=14u — scaled from 2.15u for SR > 30 mV/us)
XM9  src7 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=3.5u L=14u nf=1
XM10 src8 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=3.5u L=14u nf=1

